==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wide-angle
<hw>Wide"-an`gle</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Photog. & Optics)</fld>
<def>Having or covering an angle wider than the ordinary; -- applied to
certain lenses of relatively short focus. Lenses for ordinary purposes
have an angle of 50⟦deg⟧ or less. Wide-angle lenses may cover as much as
100⟦deg⟧ and are useful for photographing at short range, but the
pictures appear distorted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1652 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

